The same evening, Wen Jiabao and his party earnestly listened to reports by the Jiangxi Provincial Party Committee and government on Jiangxi's flood situation and its flood-fighting and relief work.
He also fully affirmed Jiangxi's preliminary victories in its flood-fighting and relief work.
Wen Jiabao pointed out: At present, the Ganjiang River's water-level is declining, but the Jiangxi Provincial Party Committee and government are still facing very arduous tasks.
Jiangxi is a major agricultural province.
While carrying out flood-fighting and relief work, we should also continually and properly handle various tasks concerning reform, stability, and development in Jiangxi.
